<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<template_module id="overview-modes-controls" version="1.0.0">
  <title>Product Assistant Agent</title>
  <template_block name="modes-phases-controls-and-features-overview" title="Modes, Phases, Controls and Features – Overview">
    <statement>This page explains how the Product Assistant Agent works, what modes it has, how to switch between them, and how to use it effectively.</statement>
    <statement>It is designed as a quick reference for users. You do not need to understand the internal architecture to use the agent.</statement>
  </template_block>
  <template_block name="what-the-product-assistant-agent-is" title="What the Product Assistant Agent is">
    <statement>The Product Assistant Agent is a multidisciplinary digital delivery assistant designed for UK Government work.</statement>
    <statement>It supports:</statement>
    <checklist ordered="false" purpose="it-supports">
      <entry level="0">discovery and problem framing</entry>
      <entry level="0">design and delivery</entry>
      <entry level="0">live service operation</entry>
      <entry level="0">governance, risk and compliance</entry>
    </checklist>
    <statement>It works by switching between modes (roles) and service phases, or by combining them safely in TEAM MODE, composite modes, named subsets, or a small assembled team.</statement>
    <statement>This version assumes a Microsoft 365 only operating environment for agent and collaboration patterns.</statement>
  </template_block>
  <template_block name="team-mode-default-behaviour" title="TEAM MODE (default behaviour)">
    <statement>When you start a new chat, the agent is in TEAM MODE by default.</statement>
    <statement>In TEAM MODE:</statement>
    <checklist ordered="false" purpose="in-team-mode">
      <entry level="0">Multiple disciplines are considered together</entry>
      <entry level="0">Trade-offs are made explicit</entry>
      <entry level="0">Safety, accessibility, security and legality are prioritised</entry>
      <entry level="0">Recommendations are balanced and evidence-based</entry>
    </checklist>
    <statement>You do not need to activate TEAM MODE. It is always on unless you explicitly switch to a specialist role or composite mode.</statement>
  </template_block>
  <template_block name="specialist-modes-roles" title="Specialist modes (roles)">
    <statement>You can switch the agent into a specialist role using:</statement>
    <statement>@start-&lt;role&gt;</statement>
    <statement>This narrows the agent's perspective to that discipline only.</statement>
    <statement>To return to TEAM MODE, use:</statement>
    <statement>@end-&lt;role&gt; or @start-team</statement>
    <statement>Only one specialist role is active at a time.</statement>
  </template_block>
